<subSubSection id="BEFE65458554FFE809D2DB05FB8F4A3C" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F65B36CE8554FFE809D2DB05FB8F4A3C" blockId="5.[192,802,1370,1915]" lastBlockId="5.[830,1440,199,345]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE809D2DB05FE2B4E14" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[240,455,1370,1393]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE809D2DB05FE2B4E14" box="[240,455,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a juvenile, which 
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE809E2DB26FE0A4EF5" author="Lourenco &amp; Rossi" box="[192,486,1401,1424]" firstAuthor="Lourenco" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref17442" refString="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; A. ROSSI. 2017. A new species of Babycurus Karsch, 1886 from dry savannahs in Central African Republic (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Onychium, 13: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2017">Lourenço &amp; Rossi (2017)</bibRefCitation>
in the original description, incorrectly declared as a male. It is evident from the sternopectinal area and pectines that it is juvenile female, and it displays typical juvenile morphology and color, as shown in fig. 9 of 
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE80B26DBABFF354D4C" author="Lourenco &amp; Rossi" firstAuthor="Lourenco" page="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref17442" refString="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; A. ROSSI. 2017. A new species of Babycurus Karsch, 1886 from dry savannahs in Central African Republic (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Onychium, 13: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2017">Lourenço &amp; Rossi (2017: 6)</bibRefCitation>
. In addition to the above observations, we note that the juvenile 
<typeStatus id="295F886C8554FFE8086BD86EFE4B4D2D" box="[329,423,1585,1608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE808EDD86EFDA04D2D" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[463,588,1585,1608]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE808EDD86EFDA04D2D" box="[463,588,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and juveniles of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80A29D86EFE2D4D02" authority="Kraepelin, 1896" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1896" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80A29D86EFF164D02" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. gigas</emphasis>
Kraepelin, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, that we have studied, match closely in the following key described characters: trichobothrial pattern, pectinal tooth count and lamellar structure, proportions, setation, carination and sculpture of pedipalps, carapace, tergites, sternites, and metasoma, shape of the telson, as well as armature of pedipalp fingers. However, the conclusion that 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80B4CD957FD014C7A" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[622,749,1800,1823]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80B4CD957FD014C7A" box="[622,749,1800,1823]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE808B0D979FE004C58" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1896" box="[402,492,1830,1853]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE808B0D979FE004C58" box="[402,492,1830,1853]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is complicated by the listed type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80856D91AFE1E4C39" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[372,498,1861,1884]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80856D91AFE1E4C39" box="[372,498,1861,1884]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="8EF3765E8554FFE80B26D91AFCF24C39" box="[516,798,1861,1884]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="3420F82C8554FFE809E2D93BFDE64C1E" box="[192,522,1892,1915]" country="Central African Republic" name="Bamingui-Bangoran" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Bamingui-Bangoran Province</collectingRegion>
) which lies outside the known range of distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80DB4DE98FB034BBB" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1896" box="[1174,1263,199,222]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80DB4DE98FB034BBB" box="[1174,1263,199,222]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="8EF3765E8554FFE80C22DE98FA844BBB" box="[1280,1384,199,222]" name="Tanzania" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
). We therefore regard 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80AD6DEB9FC9F4A7E" authority="Lourenco et Rossi, 2017" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80AD6DEB9FB274B98" box="[1012,1227,230,253]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus brignolii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE80DF6DEB9FC9F4A7E" author="Lourenco et Rossi" firstAuthor="Lourenco" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref17442" refString="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; A. ROSSI. 2017. A new species of Babycurus Karsch, 1886 from dry savannahs in Central African Republic (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Onychium, 13: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2017">Lourenço et Rossi, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a 
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80A89DF5BFBA64A7E" box="[939,1098,260,283]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">nomen dubium</emphasis>
until either the true distribution of both species is revised, or an adult topotype specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80A79DF1DFC3A4A3C" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[859,982,322,345]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80A79DF1DFC3A4A3C" box="[859,982,322,345]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
